# 1. 巨大な壁

Ken: Alright.
Ken: Like I was saying on the way over, this live house is on the same level as Rodin, where you all performed the other day.
Ken: Not only that, some of the teams you're going to see are signed to major labels. Get ready for a tough battle.
Ken: That being said... I believe you all have what it takes to win now.
An: Oh, we will.
An: Like Akito said to the entire city, we're gonna surpass RAD WEEKEND during our next event. This is all for that.
Ken: Then, give it absolutely everything you've got. Leave nothing behind.
Everyone: Right! Got it!
MC: <Next up, we've got Vivid BAD SQUAD!>
Toya: There's our cue...
Kotaro: Alright, you guys, show them what you've got! I'll do the same when I go next!
An: Yeah! We're gonna give it everything we've got!
Akito: Then, let's go!
An, Kohane & Toya: Yeah! Okay!
An: Whew! Talk about an exhausting day!!
Kohane: I'm tired too... All the other teams were so good...
Kohane: But I'm really glad we still won.
Toya: I couldn't believe it when they couldn't decide on a winner and asked us to sing another song... But that might've been our best performance yet.
Kotaro: I still can't believe how good you guys have become. I mean, you went toe-to-toe with an amazing team like them.
Akito: You say that, but try not to forget that you also went all out today.
Kotaro: Well, I figure I at least need to match you guys for passion... Since I can't match your skill, and I need to do everything I can to catch back up to you after being out of action for so long.
Akito: Yeah, we'll be counting on you.
An: Oh, Dad, that reminds me. About practice after this...
Ken: Yeah, sorry. I completely forgot that I have to go meet with the owner of COL...
Ken: You've all had a pretty taxing day, so why don't you all call it a day here?
Ken: Use this time to do whatever you like. You can practice by yourselves, work on those tasks I assigned all of you or do something else.
An: Okay, got it!
Ken: Alright, just try not to push yourselves too hard.
Akito: Okay, now what?
Toya: I'd like to work on my task... But my pitch today during the chorus is still bothering me. I think I'd like to practice that part first.
An: Okay! What are you gonna do, Kotaro?
Kotaro: I'm gonna head back and practice on my own. My little brother's been asking me to come home early when I can.
Kohane: Hehe. Your little brother must love you very much. I hope you two get to spend a lot of time together today.
Kotaro: Me too! So, I'll see you guys tomorrow!
Kohane: Then, I'll take a short break before practicing...
???: <Hey, you guys!>
Akito: Hm? That sounded like...
Akito: I had a feeling it was you, Len.
Len: <Oh, you're all here! Are you guys free to talk right now?!>
Kohane: S-Sure. But why the hurry? What's wrong?
Len: <So, the thing is...>
Len: <SEKAI has a new area!>
An, Toya & Akito: What?
Kohane: A new...area?
Len: There! Look!
An: Whoa...! This is so cool! It's like a big plaza!
Toya: You're right... This place is completely new...
Akito: It's huge. And it just appeared overnight?
Rin: Over here, you guys!
Kohane: Hi, Rin! Oh, everyone's with you!
An: So, what's the deal with this place...?
Miku: We're still not sure either. Luka just brought us over.
Kohane: I see. But how or why did just appear like this?
Luka: Hmm... I can't say for sure...
Luka: But your feelings may have something to do with it.
Akito: So, our feelings created this new area? Is that actually possible...?
MEIKO: SEKAI was born out of your feelings, so it doesn't seem like too much of a stretch to say that strong feelings can cause it to transform.
Toya: Transform...?
An: But our feelings haven't changed that much or anything...
Akito: Yeah. Our goal's still the same. To surpass RAD WEEKEND...
KAITO: True...
KAITO: Oh, but taking a look around may help us figure out what feelings went into this place being created. After all, those feelings should manifest in some way in SEKAI!
Kohane: What feelings went into this place...
Kohane: (The plaza's so big... There's a lot of graffiti on the walls—)
Kohane: Huh...?
An: Find something, Kohane?
Kohane: Oh, um... It's just that the wall of that big building over there seemed a little funny.
Toya: Yes, it is a bit odd...
Toya: Most of it is covered in flyers and graffiti, but the middle is completely devoid of anything for some reason...
An: Almost like there's a hole in it. But why...?
Akito: Yeah, it is kinda weird, but we don't have enough information to work with right now...
Akito: So, why don't we try searching for clues somewhere else?
Toya: I agree. We should get the lay of the land first... We can start with one of these alleyways.
Kohane: Oh... Okay!
Len: Whoa!! This place is totally different from the streets we're used to!
Akito: Yeah. It's like we're suddenly overseas...
Toya: Yes, this resembles the streets of Boston.
An: It does?
Toya: Yes. When I was little, my dad held a concert over there and I got to go with him. This is very similar to what I saw that time.
Kohane: Oh... Now that you mention it, one of the other alleys I saw from the plaza looked like a street in Mexico I saw in a book of photos when I was little.
Miku: Then, does that mean we're standing in the middle of a collection of streets from around the world...?
MEIKO: That may be significant.
Len: It's so cool how we get to see all these different sights! Let's keep exploring, you guys!
Rin: Hey, Len, wait up!
An: It isn't safe to rush like that, you two.
Akito: *Sigh* They never change.
Len's Voice: Huh?! Wh-What is this thing?!
Toya: ...?! What happened?!
Rin's Voice: E-Everyone, come here!
Rin's Voice: There's a huge wall blocking the way!
An: Whoa...!
Kohane: I-It's so big...!
Akito: There's plenty of buildings around here... But this wall's taller than all of them.
Toya: And it looks very sturdy. No windows or passageways either. Almost like a castle wall.
Akito: But why's this path blocked? There's no way ahead.
An: Hmm... Wanna try finding a way around it?
Toya: Yes. There were many ways out of the plaza, so one will surely take us around this.
Akito: Then, let's try that side alley over there.
Akito: I wasn't expecting to find another giant wall here...
Luka: I just tried one of the other alleys, but it was also blocked by a wall!
Toya: Could it be that all these alleyways are blocked by this one wall?
Kohane: So, we won't be able to see what's on the other side? I was hoping to see if we could find out what feelings went into making this place...
Akito: Still, what's with this wall? They don't seem natural at all.
Toya: I agree. It's as if it suddenly sprang up to block our way.
An: Did this wall also come from our feelings?
Kohane: Huh?
An: I mean, it's pretty prominent. Why else would it exist, you know?
Kohane: Right... Yes, that might be worth keeping in mind.
Kohane: But what sort of feelings would lead to this wall being created...?
Toya: If I recall correctly, it's common for walls to appear in a person's dreams when they're feeling stressed or pressured in some way.
Akito: I guess we might be feeling some pressure lately... We did say that we're going to surpass RAD WEEKEND no matter what.
An: Hmm... Which means...
An: This wall... It represents how we feel about RAD WEEKEND...?
Toya: Yes, that is a distinct possibility.
Akito: It makes sense if you think how huge it is, like no one could ever even think to try getting over it.
Kohane: Yeah...
Miku: These streets from around the world may also be relevant to that.
Kohane: Huh?
Miku: Remember what you said you're going to do after you surpass RAD WEEKEND?
An: Oh...! Right...!
An: We're gonna go beyond Aunt Nagi's dream. In other words...
An: We're gonna stand on top of the world...!
Akito: ...!
Miku: I don't know for sure, but that's my guess.
Kohane: So...
Kohane: If we do manage to surpass RAD WEEKEND, then we'll be able to see even more of SEKAI on the other side of this wall?
An: Yeah! That's gotta be it!!
Miku: I'm starting to like this place. All your dreams have a tangible shape here.
Luka: Alright! Now that we know what kind of feelings helped produce this place, let's try exploring all these alleys!
KAITO: Oh, nice idea! Strolling around streets from around the world is bound to be fun!
An: Yeah, we can visit all those streets and visualize what it'll be like when we take on the world!
Akito: Then, let's take a walk. I do wanna go back and check out that last alley.
Toya: Me too. I'm still curious about the one I spotted from the plaza earlier.
Kohane: Oh, there's also one that caught my eye...
An: Hmm... Checking out all of them is gonna take pretty long, so why don't we split up and meet back in the plaza later?
Akito: Sounds good. That way, we'll still be able to have practice.
Toya: Then, let's give ourselves thirty minutes to explore and meet back in the plaza afterwards.
Kohane: Okay!
